From eae275fceb7cc8d395af09e64307cb1f0556bd22 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Felicitas Pojtinger <felicitas@pojtinger.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Apr 2026 22:33:15 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] docs: Use `.sysext.raw` consistently following https://uapi-group.org/specifications/specs/discoverable_disk_image/#naming

Signed-off-by: Felicitas Pojtinger <felicitas@pojtinger.com>
---
diff --git a/docs/contributing-os.md b/docs/contributing-os.md
index fc8a98afffbe3f5668f7717520da7939e47da5c0..425230f69ce8ffb5700be17172f93b74e804cd52 100644
--- a/docs/contributing-os.md
+++ b/docs/contributing-os.md
@@ -118,7 +118,7 @@
 To remove the system extension from your local workstation, run the following:
 
 ```shell
-$ run0 rm /var/lib/extensions/zz-gnome-control-center.raw
+$ run0 rm /var/lib/extensions/zz-gnome-control-center.sysext.raw
 $ run0 systemd-sysext refresh --force
 ```
 
@@ -164,7 +164,7 @@
 To remove the system extension from the target, run the following:
 
 ```shell
-$ ssh $SSH_ARGS run0 rm /var/lib/extensions/zz-gnome-control-center.raw
+$ ssh $SSH_ARGS run0 rm /var/lib/extensions/zz-gnome-control-center.sysext.raw
 $ ssh $SSH_ARGS run0 systemd-sysext refresh --force
 ```
 

